article.headline: Boston College 99, Maine 61
article.story: BOSTON -- Corey Raji went 12-for-12 from the floor and scored a career-high 26 points to lead Boston College to its seventh straight win, 99-61 over Maine on Tuesday afternoon. Tyrese Rice added 21 points in limited playing time for the Eagles (10-2). Joe Trapani scored 15 points and Rakim Sanders had 12 points and seven assists. Gerald McLemore led the Black Bears (5-7) with 18 points. BC failed to reach the century mark, despite having 94 points with more than four minutes left in the game. In an atmosphere that resembled a preseason scrimmage more than a regular season game -- with only about a thousand fans in attendance due to a rare early afternoon starting time -- the Eagles used first-half runs of 11-0 and 12-0 to give them a 50-26 halftime edge. BC pushed its advantage to 40 points, 94-54, on Reggie Jackson's basket with 4:14 left.
